---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import { withBase } from '../../lib/paths';

const tree = `axon/
  policy.py      # PolicyEngine: allow/ask/deny, filesystem jail, non-overridable deny layer
  client.py      # Ollama over HTTP (stdlib only). Validates tool-call shape.
  session.py     # state: messages, step counter, token budget, redundancy caches
  loop.py        # the agentic loop + four cuts: done / max_steps / stalled / repetition
  dispatch.py    # single path for tools: cache, repetition nudge, budget, transcript
  prompt.py      # TemplatedSystemInstructions (fixed security scaffold + injectable role)
  tools/         # read_file, write_file, list_dir, run_shell, run_tests, start_subagent, done
  artifacts.py   # the structured, verifiable transcript (artifacts over raw logs)`;

const cuts = [
  {
    name: 'done',
    trigger: 'The model calls done(summary, verified=true).',
    detail: 'The only successful exit. Verification is mandatory: the agent must run the tests or the command and call done only with evidence.',
  },
  {
    name: 'max_steps',
    trigger: 'The step counter reaches the policy limit (default 25).',
    detail: 'A hard ceiling on loop iterations. Near the limit the harness injects a synthesis prompt so the agent reports what it has rather than dying silently.',
  },
  {
    name: 'stalled',
    trigger: 'Two text-only turns with no tool call.',
    detail: 'A text-only turn is ambiguous. The harness nudges once ("Did you finish? Call done, or call a tool"). A second text-only turn cuts as stalled.',
  },
  {
    name: 'repetition_detected',
    trigger: 'Three identical tool calls in a row.',
    detail: 'Catches the re-read loop where a model keeps reading the same file. The dispatcher also serves idempotent reads from cache and nudges before the cut fires.',
  },
];

const tools = [
  { name: 'read_file', kind: 'read', desc: 'Read a file from the workspace, returned with line numbers. Idempotent: served from cache on a repeat call.' },
  { name: 'write_file', kind: 'write', desc: 'Create or overwrite a file. Creates parent dirs. Backs up before overwriting.' },
  { name: 'list_dir', kind: 'read', desc: 'List files and subdirectories. Preferred over ls through run_shell. Cacheable.' },
  { name: 'run_shell', kind: 'shell', desc: 'Run a command. Passes through the PolicyEngine first. Timeout 60s default, 300s max.' },
  { name: 'run_tests', kind: 'shell', desc: 'Run the test suite (pytest -q by default). The verification primitive of the loop.' },
  { name: 'start_subagent', kind: 'control', desc: 'Spawn a read-only subagent with an isolated context. Returns only its synthesis. Depth capped at 1.' },
  { name: 'done', kind: 'control', desc: 'Terminate the loop with a summary and a verified flag. The only successful exit.' },
];
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Architecture"
  eyebrow="How it works"
  description="The agentic loop, the four termination cuts, and the toolset. A while-loop, never recursive, with the harness behaviours the model cannot be trusted to do."
>
  <h2>The loop</h2>
  <p>
    axon works in a single while-loop: plan, use a tool, execute, verify, repeat. It is
    never recursive. Recursion happens only inside subagents, which run their own bounded
    loop. Each iteration the loop sends the conversation to the model, reads back tool
    calls, dispatches them, and appends the results to the transcript. The loop owns the
    four cuts that decide when to stop.
  </p>

  <div class="loop-beats" role="list">
    <div role="listitem" class="beat"><span class="beat-n">1</span><strong>Plan</strong><span>State the next move in one or two lines.</span></div>
    <div role="listitem" class="beat"><span class="beat-n">2</span><strong>Use a tool</strong><span>Call read, write, shell, tests or a subagent.</span></div>
    <div role="listitem" class="beat"><span class="beat-n">3</span><strong>Execute</strong><span>The dispatcher runs it through the policy gate.</span></div>
    <div role="listitem" class="beat"><span class="beat-n">4</span><strong>Verify</strong><span>Run the tests. No done() without evidence.</span></div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Verification is the beat that separates an agent from autocomplete. The model cannot
    self-evaluate reliably, so verification is a step the harness forces: <code>done()</code>
    is only accepted with evidence that tests pass or a command ran.
  </p>

  <h2>The four cuts</h2>
  <p>
    A cut is a termination condition. Exactly one fires per run. The loop returns a
    <code>LoopResult</code> carrying the reason, the step count and the full session.
  </p>

  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Cut</th>
          <th scope="col">Trigger</th>
          <th scope="col">What it prevents</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {cuts.map((c) => (
          <tr>
            <th scope="row"><code>{c.name}</code></th>
            <td>{c.trigger}</td>
            <td class="muted">{c.detail}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>The toolset</h2>
  <p>
    Seven tools, exposed to Ollama as JSON schemas. Reads are idempotent and cacheable.
    Writes are backed up. Shell goes through the policy gate. The subagent runs read-only
    in an isolated context so heavy reads do not pollute the parent window.
  </p>

  <div class="tool-grid">
    {tools.map((t) => (
      <div class="tool">
        <div class="tool-head">
          <code class="tool-name">{t.name}</code>
          <span class={`tool-tag tag-${t.kind}`}>{t.kind}</span>
        </div>
        <p class="muted">{t.desc}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>The dispatcher</h2>
  <p>
    Every tool runs through one path: <code>dispatch.py</code>. It wraps each handler with
    the cross-cutting behaviours the model cannot be trusted to do on its own.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Redundancy cache.</strong> Identical idempotent reads are served from cache, killing the re-read loop.</li>
    <li><strong>Repetition nudge.</strong> After two repeats the result carries a nudge to move on, a softer defence before the repetition cut fires.</li>
    <li><strong>Token accounting.</strong> Each result is charged against a budget. Near the limit the loop forces a synthesis.</li>
    <li><strong>Structured transcript.</strong> Calls and results are logged as artifacts, not raw stdout, so the run is inspectable.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The file map</h2>
  <CodeBlock code={tree} lang="text" label="package layout" />

  <h2>Why these decisions</h2>
  <p>Each design choice is grounded in AI-engineering literature, not vibes.</p>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Decision</th>
          <th scope="col">Why</th>
          <th scope="col">Source</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Harness, not just model</th>
          <td>A better harness beats a better model on the same task.</td>
          <td class="muted">harness-design research</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Verify in the loop</th>
          <td>Agents cannot self-evaluate reliably; verification must be a step.</td>
          <td class="muted">Ning et al. 2026</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Security framing in the prompt</th>
          <td>Framing the agent as a senior security engineer reduces vulnerable output.</td>
          <td class="muted">Pearce et al. 2022 (IEEE S&P)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">The model is untrusted input</th>
          <td>All security lives in the policy engine and jail, never in the prompt.</td>
          <td class="muted">OWASP LLM Top 10</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Subagents for context isolation</th>
          <td>Offload heavy reads; the parent keeps a clean window.</td>
          <td class="muted">Antigravity's start_subagent</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p>
    Next: how the <a href={withBase('/docs/safety')}>PolicyEngine</a> gates every action,
    or the <a href={withBase('/docs/evaluation')}>evaluation protocol</a> behind the
    completion claims.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .loop-beats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin: 1.6em 0;
  }

  .beat {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: #fffdfa;
  }

  .beat-n {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--teal);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .beat strong {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }

  .beat span:last-child {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .tool-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(15rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.6em 0;
  }

  .tool {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    background: #fffdfa;
  }

  .tool-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .tool-name {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    background: var(--cream-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--teal-deep);
    padding: 0.12em 0.45em;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }

  .tool p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .tool-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.16em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }

  .tag-read { background: var(--wash-blue); color: var(--ink); }
  .tag-write { background: var(--peach); color: var(--ink); }
  .tag-shell { background: var(--wash-green); color: var(--ink); }
  .tag-control { background: var(--cream-2); color: var(--ink-muted); border: 1px solid var(--border); }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .loop-beats {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
